From ac7174604ec84c1fba468dc1f66366a01c1ed8ff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 16 Jul 2025 12:02:32 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: wifi: ath12k: Add client SP mode support
 for PSD and EIRP-based reg TPC

Add support for computing and populating regulatory TPC information for
stations operating in 6 GHz Standard Power (SP) mode.

Extend the reg_tpc_info structure to include tpe_psd[] and tpe_eirp[]
arrays, which hold PSD and EIRP-based TPE values. Derive reg_6g_power_mode
for STA and handle client SP mode using NL80211_REG_REGULAR_CLIENT_SP + 1.

For PSD-based TPC, use the pre-filled tpe_psd[] array and regulatory PSD
limits to compute min(TPE, reg) per sub-channel. Finalize these values
using ath12k_mac_finalize_psd_table() and store them in
chan_psd_power_info[].

For EIRP-based TPC, derive EIRP from the minimum of tpe_psd[], tpe_eirp[],
and reg_eirp[] for each supported bandwidth. Store the result in
chan_eirp_power_info[].

Enable transmit power control for client SP mode and align STA-side
behavior with existing AP SP logic. Limit client SP mode support to fixed
devices only; mobile devices (e.g., WCN7850) are not supported.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
ath12k/0420-e-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-ath12k-Add-WMI-support-for-sending.patch

